The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Good Morning
                                                                                                               Good Morning
      Hello It's Thursday , April 3 , 2008                    
	Campus fest     Heritage Institute of Technology and t2 present Day I of Eclecia08, on the campus, 10.30am.    
	Films    Screening of Italian films Io Non Ho Paura (I Am Not Scared) by Gabriele Salvatores and Limperatore Di Capri (The Emperor Of Capri) by Luigi Comencini at Nandan, 4pm and 6.30pm, respectively.    
	Yoga    Yoga camp for children at Solace, 4 Sunny Park, 10.30am to 11.30am.    
	Fashion    Summer collection of     extiles at Artisana, Crafts Council of West Bengal, Chowringhee Terrace, 10am to 7.30pm.    
	Art watch    On the Verge, recent works by Sumitro Basak, at CIMA Gallery, 2pm to 7pm.    An exhibition of sculptures by Manjushri Chakraborty and S. Kumar Deb at Academy of Fine Arts, 3pm to 8pm.    Structures, a collection of Somenath Maitys works, at Gallery Sanskriti, 11am to 8pm.    A group exhibition of paintings at The Palladian Lounge, noon to 8pm.    Butterfly Effect, an abstract show, at Ganges Art Gallery, 11am to 7pm.     Revelation 2008 at Birla Academy of Art and Culture, 3pm to 8pm.     An exhibition of paintings by Murshida Arzu Alpana at Chitrakoot Art Gallery, 3pm to 8pm.     India Shining India Crying, a photography exhibition by Johann Rousselot, at Bose Pacia, 11am to 7pm.    An exhibition of works by Dilip Chaudhury at Taj Bengal, 10am to 11pm.    A show of works by Partha Pratim Deb at Gallery K2, 11am to 7pm.    Fresco painting workshop 2008 at Chitra Bhavan, 11am to 5pm.                                                                                                                                                                   
